<li id="cite_note-20"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-20">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The exact number of negative votes is unknown. In his memoirs <a href="/w/index.php?title=Anastas_Mikoian&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Anastas Mikoian (page does not exist)">Anastas Mikoian</a> writes that out of 1225 delegates, around 270 voted against Stalin and that the official number of negative votes was given as three, with the rest of ballots destroyed. Following Khrushchev's secret speech in 1956, a commission of the central committee investigated the votes and found that 267 ballots were missing.</span></li>
